package Collection.Queue.Extends.Deque;

public class Document {

 /*✅ What is Deque in Java?
Deque stands for Double-Ended Queue.
It is a linear data structure that allows insertion and deletion of elements from both ends:
From the front (head)
From the rear (tail)*/


    /*| Feature                    | Queue                                                                                         | Deque (Double-Ended Queue)                                                                                                                  |
| -------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Definition**             | A linear data structure that follows **FIFO (First-In-First-Out)** principle.                 | A linear data structure that allows **insertion and deletion at both ends** (front and rear).                                               |
| **Insertion**              | Allowed **only at the rear (tail)**.                                                          | Allowed at **both front and rear**.                                                                                                         |
| **Removal**                | Allowed **only from the front (head)**.                                                       | Allowed from **both front and rear**.                                                                                                       |
| **Access**                 | You can only access the **front (peek) and rear indirectly (by inserting)**.                  | You can access **both front and rear** directly using peek methods.                                                                         |
| **Common Implementations** | - `LinkedList`<br> - `PriorityQueue`<br> - `ArrayBlockingQueue`<br> - `ConcurrentLinkedQueue` | - `ArrayDeque`<br> - `LinkedList`<br> - `ConcurrentLinkedDeque`                                                                             |
| **Methods**                | - `add()`, `offer()`<br> - `remove()`, `poll()`<br> - `peek()`, `element()`                   | - `addFirst()`, `addLast()`<br> - `removeFirst()`, `removeLast()`<br> - `peekFirst()`, `peekLast()`<br> - `push()`, `pop()` (stack support) |
| **Usage**                  | Suitable when you need **strict FIFO** operations.                                            | Suitable when you need **more flexible insertion/removal** from both ends or stack-like behavior.                                           |
| **Real-Life Analogy**      | People standing in a queue: join from the back, leave from the front.                         | People standing in a line where some may join or leave from either end.                                                                     |
*/

}
